{"lemma": "عازِبٌ", "slug": "عازِبٌ", "root": "ع.ز.ب", "root_slug": "ع-ز-ب", "root_link": "/words/roots/ع-ز-ب", "pos": "ADJ", "pos_camel": "adj", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 1}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n28946"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%B2%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "bachelor", "fa": "مجرد", "ur": "بے شوہر", "tr": "bekâr", "id": "lajang", "bn": "অবিবাহিত", "es": "soltero", "fr": "célibataire", "de": "Junggeselle", "ru": "холостяк", "zh": "单身汉"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "bachelor"}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/ʕaː.zib/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n28946", "headword_ar": "عَازِبٌ", "root": "Ezb", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Distant,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "remote:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb, TA:) applied in this sense to herbage: (S, K:) or, applied to herbage,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as has not been depastured at all, nor trodden:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and, accord. to the A, only"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as is in a desert in which is no seed-produce:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) and it is likewise applied to meadows ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rawoDN", "text_ar": "رَوْضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") [app. as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "distant,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "remote"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaziybN", "text_ar": "عَزِيبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (A, TA.) In the following saying,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "waSadorK A^araAHa All~ayolu EaAziba ham~ihi\n                      \n                     \n                        taDaAEafa fiyhi AlHuzonu mino kul~i jaAnibi"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "In many a bosom whose remote"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "long-past"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "anxiety night has brought back, grief has multiplied from every quarter"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], it is used metaphorically. (A.) And [in like manner,] in a trad. of 'Átikeh,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "qahun~a hawaA='N waAlHuluwmu EawaAzibu"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And they are devoid of reason, the intel-lects"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[being]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "far away:"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EawaAzibu", "text_ar": "عَوَازِبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "here being pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAzibN", "text_ar": "عَازِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (L, TA.) And [in a similar manner,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EawaAzibu AlA^aTohaAri", "text_ar": "عَوَازِبُ الاَطْهَارِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[in which"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EawaAzibu", "text_ar": "عَوَازِبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAzibapN", "text_ar": "عَازِبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is applied as an epithet to women whose husbands are absent: (S and O and TA, from a verse of En-Ná- bighah Edh-Dhubyánee: [for the lit. meaning, see 1, latter half:]) ―         -b2-  [for]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAzibN", "text_ar": "عَازِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Absent;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "concealed."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb.) ―         -b3-  It is also applied to sheep or goats, ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aA='N", "text_ar": "شَا=ءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", O, TA, and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ganamN", "text_ar": "غَنَمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", O,) and to camels, ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ibilN", "text_ar": "اـِبِلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", O,) meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Remote in the pasturage,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that do not return in the evening,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that do not repair to the place of alighting and abode"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of their owners"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the night:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) and [in like manner] ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EazabN", "text_ar": "عَزَبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is applied to cattle, or camels &c., ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maAlN", "text_ar": "مَالٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", A, O, TA,) meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that go away to a distance from their owners."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O.) See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaziybN", "text_ar": "عَزِيبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[which, thus applied, is a quasi-pl. n. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAzibN", "text_ar": "عَازِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAzibapN", "text_ar": "عَازِبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is likewise applied to camels (O, K) as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "That go far away to pasture:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, K: *) so in the prov."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~amaA", "text_ar": "اـِنَّمَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@$otarayotu Alganama Hi*aAra AlEaAzibapi", "text_ar": "ا@شْتَرَيْتُ الغَنَمَ حِذَارَ العَازِبَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I only bought the sheep,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "goats, in fear of loosing those that go far away to pasture"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: said by a man who had camels, and sold them, and bought sheep, or goats, lest they [the camels] should go far away to pasture; and his sheep, or goats, did so: (O, K:) it is applied to the case of him who acts with gentleness [or precaution] in the easiest of affairs, and has unexpected difficulty, or trouble, inseparable from him. (O.) ―         -b4-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EazabN", "text_ar": "عَزَبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in three places. ―         -b5-  And see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muEaz~ibapN", "text_ar": "مُعَزِّبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": ["Msb", "TA", "S", "K", "O"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}